def data_research(dataset):
    #  5    .
    display(dataset.head())
    display(dataset.tail())
    print()
    
    #    .
    display(HTML('<h3>   </h3><br>'))
    print(dataset.info())
    
    #    .
    display(HTML('<h3> </h3><br>'))
    print(dataset.columns)
    
    #      .
    display(HTML('<br><h3>    </h3><br>'))
    if dataset.isna().sum().any():
        display(HTML(
            f'<b>    : </b>'
            f'{dataset.isna().sum().sum()} '
            f'({round((dataset.isna().sum().sum() / (dataset.shape[0] * dataset.shape[1]) * 100), 1)}%)<br>'
        ))
        
        display(HTML(
            f'<b>,     : </b>'
            f'{dataset[dataset.columns].isna().any(axis=1).sum()} '
            f'({round((dataset[dataset.columns].isna().any(axis=1).sum() / dataset.shape[0] * 100), 1)}%)<br>'
        ))
        
        display(HTML('<b>    : </b>'))
        display(pd.DataFrame({
            'count': dataset.isna().sum(),
            '%': dataset.isna().mean() * 100
        }).style.set_precision(1).background_gradient('YlGnBu'))
    else:
        print(' ')
    
    #    .
    display(HTML('<br><h3>   </h3><br>'))
    if dataset.duplicated().sum() != 0:
        print(f': {dataset.duplicated().sum()} '
              f'({(dataset.duplicated().sum() / dataset.shape[0]):.2%} '
              f'  )')
    else:
        print('  ')
    
    #    .
    display(HTML('<br><h3>   </h3><br>'))
    for column in dataset.columns:
        display(HTML(
            f'<b>    "{column}": </b>'
            f'{len(dataset[column].unique())}'
        ))
        print(dataset.sort_values(by=column)[column].unique())

def research_plot(dataset):
    #      .
    if len(num_col(dataset)) != 0:
        #     .
        display(HTML('<br><h3>  </h3>'))
        display(dataset.describe(datetime_is_numeric=True))

        #     .
        display(HTML('<br><h3>   </h3><br>'))
        num_plots = len(num_col(dataset))
        #   .
        num_rows = (num_plots + 1) // 2 * 2
        #    .
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(num_rows, 2, figsize=(14, 3 * num_rows))

        #     .
        for i, column in enumerate(num_col(dataset)):
            row = (i // 2) * 2
            col = i % 2

            # .
            sns.histplot(
                data=dataset,
                x=column,
                bins=20,
                kde=True,
                ax=axes[row, col]
            )
            axes[row, col].grid(True)
            axes[row, col].set_xlabel(column)
            axes[row, col].set_ylabel(' ')
            axes[row, col].set_title(
                f'  \n'
                f'    {column}'
            )

            #  .
            box_data = dataset[column]
            #     - datetime64.
            if np.issubdtype(dataset[column].dtype, np.datetime64):
                #     .
                if box_data.isna().any():
                    #  .
                    box_data = box_data.dropna()
                #     .
                box_data = pd.DataFrame(pd.to_numeric(box_data))

            #   .
            sns.boxplot(
                data=box_data,
                orient='h',
                ax=axes[row + 1, col]
            )
            axes[row + 1, col].grid(True)
            axes[row + 1, col].set_xlabel(column)
            axes[row + 1, col].set_yticks([])

        #    ,
        #    .
        if num_plots % 2 != 0:
            fig.delaxes(axes[-1, -1])
            fig.delaxes(axes[-2, -1])

        #  .
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

    #      .
    if len(cat_col(dataset)) != 0:
        #     .
        display(HTML('<br><h3>   </h3><br>'))
        #     ID.
        for column in cat_col(dataset):
            #     .
            sorted_counts = dataset[column].value_counts(ascending=True)
            #     .
            fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 6))

            #   -  .
            axs[0].barh(
                sorted_counts.index,
                sorted_counts.values,
                color=sns.color_palette('pastel')
            )
            axs[0].set_xlabel('')
            axs[0].yaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=45)
            #     .
            for index, value in enumerate(sorted_counts.values):
                axs[0].text(value, index, str(value))

            #   -  .
            axs[1].pie(
                sorted_counts.values,
                labels=sorted_counts.index,
                colors=sns.color_palette('pastel'),
                autopct='%1.1f%%'
            )
            plt.suptitle(
                f'      "{column}"'
            )
            plt.tight_layout()
            plt.show()

def num_hue_plot(dataset, num_column, cat_column):
    #      .
    result = pd.DataFrame()
    #      .
    for i in dataset[cat_column].unique():
        #      .
        desc = (
            dataset[dataset[cat_column] == i]
            [num_column].describe(datetime_is_numeric=True)
        )
        #    DataFrame   .
        desc_df = pd.DataFrame(desc).transpose()
        #      .
        desc_df.index = [i]
        #     DataFrame.
        result = pd.concat([result, desc_df])
        
    display(HTML(
        f'<br><h4>       '
        f'"{num_column}"     "{cat_column}"</h4>'
    ))
    display(result)
    
    #   
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    sns.histplot(
        data=dataset,
        x=num_column,
        hue=cat_column,
        alpha=0.4,
        kde=True,
        bins=20,
        stat='density',
        common_norm=False
    )
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.xlabel('')
    plt.ylabel(' ')
    plt.show()
    
    #     
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 3))
    box_data = dataset[num_column]
    if np.issubdtype(dataset[num_column].dtype, np.datetime64):
        if box_data.isna().any():
            box_data = box_data.dropna()
        box_data = pd.to_numeric(box_data)
    sns.boxplot(data=dataset, x=box_data, y=cat_column)
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()

def stacked_plot(dataset, features, target):
    #   ,    
    dataset_copy = dataset.copy()
    
    #   
    le = LabelEncoder()
    dataset_copy[target] = le.fit_transform(dataset_copy[target])
    
    #    
    avg_churn_rate = dataset_copy[target].mean()
    num_plots = len(features)
    
    for i in range(0, num_plots, 2):
        fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 5))
        for j in range(2):
            if i + j < num_plots:
                sns.barplot(
                    x=features[i + j],
                    y=target,
                    data=dataset_copy,
                    palette='pastel',
                    ax=axs[j]
                )
                axs[j].axhline(y=avg_churn_rate, color='red', linestyle='--')
                axs[j].xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90)
                axs[j].set_title(f'   '
                                 f' "{features[i + j]}"')
                #   
                for p in axs[j].patches:
                    height = p.get_height()
                    axs[j].annotate(
                        f'{height:.1%}',
                        (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2, height / 2),
                        ha='center',
                        va='bottom'
                    )
        if num_plots % 2 != 0 and i + 1 == num_plots:
            fig.delaxes(axs[1])
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

def vif(dataset):
    display(HTML('<h3>   (VIF)</h3>'))
    vif_df = pd.DataFrame()
    vif_df['feature'] = dataset.columns
    vif_df['VIF'] = [
        variance_inflation_factor(dataset.values, i)
        for i in range(dataset.shape[1])
    ]
    display(vif_df.sort_values(by='VIF', ascending=False).style.background_gradient('YlGnBu'))

#      
def count_additional_services(row):
    services = [
        row['online_security'],
        row['online_backup'],
        row['device_protection'],
        row['tech_support'],
        row['streaming_tv'],
        row['streaming_movies'],
        row['multiple_lines']
    ]
    return sum(1 for service in services if service == 'Yes')

def customer_profile_analysis(dataset, target):
    #     :    
    churn = dataset[dataset[target] == 'Yes']
    no_churn = dataset[dataset[target] == 'No']

    summary = {}

    for column in dataset.columns:
        if column == target:
            continue

        if dataset[column].dtype in [np.float64, np.int64]:
            churn_stat = churn[column].mean()
            no_churn_stat = no_churn[column].mean()
            relative_difference = (churn_stat - no_churn_stat) / no_churn_stat
        else:
            churn_stat = churn[column].mode()[0]
            no_churn_stat = no_churn[column].mode()[0]
            #     
            relative_difference = 'N/A'  

        summary[column] = {
            '': churn_stat,
            ' ': no_churn_stat,
            ' ': relative_difference
        }

    summary_df = pd.DataFrame(summary).T
    return summary_df

    columns=[
        'Model', 
        'Training Time', 
        'Prediction Time',
        'ROC-AUC',

    ]
)

best_model_params = None

    GridSearchCV    ,     .











In [92]:



     


for model in tqdm(models, desc="Total Progress"):
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(
        model['model_pipeline'],
        param_grid=model['param_grid'],
        cv=3,
        scoring=['roc_auc', 'accuracy'],
        refit='roc_auc'
    )

    start_time = time.time()
    grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)
    training_time = time.time() - start_time

    best_estimator = grid_search.best_estimator_
    best_params = grid_search.best_params_

    start_time = time.time()
    y_pred = best_estimator.predict(X_train)
    prediction_time = time.time() - start_time

    roc_auc = grid_search.cv_results_['mean_test_roc_auc'][
        grid_search.best_index_
    ]
    accuracy = grid_search.cv_results_['mean_test_accuracy'][
        grid_search.best_index_
    ]

    results = results.append({
        'Model': model['name'],
        'Training Time': training_time,
        'Prediction Time': prediction_time,
        'ROC-AUC': roc_auc,
        'Accuracy': accuracy
    }, ignore_index=True)

    if roc_auc > best_roc_auc:
        best_roc_auc = roc_auc
        best_model = best_estimator
        best_model_params = best_params
